comment_data.body: Return here? I think emitting the error logs it but doesn't crash the program
@demipixel ~~I just moved the error thing to another line?~~ It wasn't in the original code, so I thought that was how it worked.
Well the "else" meant it wouldn't run the collect code if it threw an error. So that means you have to add a return inside the "if" if you're not using "else".
put the release number here instead ( "0.0.0" ) : for both prismarine-item and prismarine-windows
use require("../version") instead of "1.8" (so we don't have to change the version number everywhere when we move to 1.9)

this should be in a player plugins
and use the "windowUpdate" event instead of creating a new "inventoryChange" event (see https://github.com/PrismarineJS/prismarine-windows#window-windowupdate-slot-olditem-newitem )
better call it emptySlot. Identifiers starting by a capital letter are class name.
The reason I put the repository is because they weren't published when I wrote this.

nah, the whole point of using that event is that it is already emitted by prismarine-windows (see https://github.com/PrismarineJS/prismarine-windows/blob/master/lib/windows.js#L203)

and it's not an event of entity or player, it's an event of player.inventory
newItem. capital letter is for classes
nah itemStack is indeed ItemStack (might want to call it Item though)
